cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM

The paper deals with the problem of abductive reasoning, which is a fundamental problem in artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves a thorough analysis of the parameterised complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also uses Schaefer's constraint satisfaction framework, which is a well-known tool in computational complexity theory, indicating that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
